excerpt: Recreational lake featuring colorful houseboats, shoreline gardens, parks & trails & boat rides.
detail_description: Dal Lake is a popular recreational spot known for its vibrant houseboats, scenic gardens, and leisurely boat rides. Visitors can enjoy exciting tours and cruises on the picturesque lake, with options for overnight stays on houseboats or sightseeing tours around Srinagar. Various tour packages offer hassle-free booking of accommodations in Srinagar hotels, ensuring a comfortable and memorable stay. Additionally, nearby attractions such as Nehru Park and Kathi Darwaza are easily accessible from the lake area.
name: Dal Lake
address: Srinagar

excerpt: Believed to have been built in 371 B.C., this is one of India's most important places of pilgrimage.
detail_description: Perched atop the scenic Shankaracharya hill, Shri Shankaracharya Temple is a significant pilgrimage site in India. Believed to have been constructed in 371 B.C., this ancient temple is dedicated to Lord Shiva, the deity of destruction and meditation. It is said that Adi Shankaracharya achieved spiritual enlightenment here before founding the four Hindu schools of Advaita philosophy. Visitors can climb 243 steps to reach the top and enjoy breathtaking views of the valley below.
name: Shri Shankaracharya Temple
address: Durgjan, Srinagar, Jammu and Kashmir 190001

excerpt: Built in the 17th century, this terraced garden offers view of Dal Lake & a stone dwelling.
detail_description: Pari Mahal, a stunning historical monument located above the Chashma Shahi Gardens in Srinagar, is a major highlight of the city known for its architectural brilliance. This grand seven-terraced palace sits atop the Zabarwan Mountain range and offers breathtaking views of Dal Lake and the surrounding mountains. Built in the 17th century by Dara Shikoh, it is a perfect blend of Islamic and Persian architecture.
name: Pari Mahal
address: 3VJG+FVC, near Pari Mahal Parking, Srinagar, Jammu and Kashmir 190001

excerpt: Tranquil 1.7-mile-long lake with a mountain backdrop, houseboats & restaurants on its leafy shores.
detail_description: Nigeen Lake, nestled next to the famous Dal Lake in Srinagar, offers a serene and picturesque retreat for visitors. Surrounded by lush greenery and with a stunning mountain backdrop, this 1.7-mile-long lake is dotted with charming houseboats and inviting restaurants along its leafy shores. It provides a more secluded and intimate experience compared to Dal Lake, making it an ideal destination for those seeking tranquility amidst the breathtaking landscapes of Kashmir.
name: Nigeen Lake
address: Srinagar 190006

excerpt: Sprawling Mughal garden complex featuring numerous terraces, channels & richly landscaped greens.
detail_description: Shalimar Bagh Mughal Garden is a magnificent complex with terraces, channels, and lush greenery. It is the largest of the three stunning Mughal Gardens in Srinagar, built by Emperor Jahangir in 1619 for his wife Noor Jahan. The garden offers breathtaking views of Dal Lake and showcases exquisite Mughal horticultural craftsmanship.
name: Shalimar Garden
address: Chinar chowk, Shalimar, Srinagar, Jammu and Kashmir 191121

excerpt: Lakeside mosque & pilgrimage site with Himalaya views, plus gardens & street food stalls.
detail_description: Nestled on the picturesque northern shores of Dal Lake in Srinagar, the Dargah Hazratbal Shrine stands as a beacon of spirituality and architectural beauty. This revered mosque, crafted from stunning white marble, is not only a pilgrimage site for Muslims but also an iconic landmark that draws visitors from around the world. The shrine is home to a sacred relic believed to be a hair strand of Prophet Muhammad, enhancing its significance among devotees.
name: Dargah Hazratbal Shrine
address: Dargah Hazratbal Mosque, University Main Road, Hazaratbal, Srinagar, Jammu and Kashmir 190006

excerpt: Bucolic garden & freshwater springs, with landscaped terraced greens, waterfalls & fountains.

name: Chashme Shahi Garden
address: 7, Boulevard Road, Chashma Shahi, Rainawari, Srinagar, Jammu and Kashmir 190001

excerpt: Hill with dramatic city views & a variety of structures, including a Hindu temple & a fort.

name: Hari Parbat
address: Nohata, Srinagar, Jammu and Kashmir 190003

detail_description: Nestled within the enchanting Dal Lake in Srinagar, Char Chinar is a captivating island adorned with four magnificent Chinar trees. name: Char Chinar Dal lake

address: 2PRV+R8H, Batahar, Jammu and Kashmir 91111

address: Jammu and Kashmir, Cheshma Shahi Rd, Rainawari, Srinagar, Jammu and Kashmir 190001

excerpt: Srinagar is a city in Indian-administered Jammu and Kashmir in the disputed Kashmir region. It is the largest city and summer capital of Jammu and Kashmir, which is an Indian-administered union territory. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Srinagar, the largest city and summer capital of Jammu and Kashmir, is a captivating destination nestled in the heart of the picturesque Kashmir region. Recognized as a UNESCO Creative City since 2021, it enchants visitors with its stunning landscapes and vibrant culture. A must-do is to glide across Dal Lake on a traditional shikara while soaking in views of majestic mountains.
name: Srinagar

detail_description: Masjid Dastgeer Sahib, a historic shrine located in the heart of Khanyar, Srinagar, is a testament to the rich spiritual heritage of the region. Established in 1845 and later expanded in 1877, this remarkable Sufi sanctuary honors Sheikh Syed Abdul Qadir Jelan. Visitors are drawn to its significant relics, including strands of hair from the revered saint and an ancient Quran believed to be penned by Hazrat Ali on musk deer skin.
name: Masjid Dastgeer Sahib
address: 3RV8+8V5, Khaniyar, Srinagar, Jammu and Kashmir 190003

detail_description: Shikara Ride Ghat No.1 is a popular attraction located 4 km from Srinagar's city center. It offers a mesmerizing experience as visitors embark on a serene boat ride along the iconic waterways of Dal Lake and Jhelum River. The hour-long ride allows up to four people per boat, providing breathtaking views of the surrounding mountains, Mughal gardens, and vibrant floating markets.
name: Shikara Ride Ghat No.1
address: Shikara Stand, No 1, Boulevard Rd, Karapura, Rainawari, Srinagar, Jammu and Kashmir 190001

detail_description: Anchar Lake is a picturesque shallow water body located 10 kilometers northwest of Srinagar city, surrounded by a mix of rural and urban characteristics. Fed by channels from the Sind nallah and connected to Khushal sar lake and Nigin lake, it offers a serene environment for relaxation. During winter, visitors can witness exotic bird species that migrate to the area. Despite political tensions in the region, Anchar Lake remains a place of natural beauty and tranquility where visitors can create cherished memories.
name: Anchar Lake

excerpt: Established in 1898, this museum houses archaeological items, weapons, paintings, textiles & more.
detail_description: The SPS Museum, also known as Sri Pratap Singh museum, has been a prominent attraction in Srinagar since its establishment in 1898. The museum boasts an extensive collection of archaeological items, weapons, paintings, textiles and more. Additionally, it features an open-air archaeology gallery that adds to the allure of the complex. This renowned museum is frequented by both locals and foreigners due to its royal and ancient archaeological displays.
name: SPS Museum
address: Lal Mandi, Srinagar, Jammu and Kashmir 190008

detail_description: Ziyarat Hazrat Makhdoom Sahib RA, also known as Hamza Makhdoom Kashmiri, was a Sufi mystic and scholar who played a significant role in spreading Islam in Kashmir. name: Zeyarat Hazrat Makhdoom Sahib RA
address: Makhdoom Sahib 7889678485 Kashmir Makhdoom Sahib, Jammu and Kashmir 190003

excerpt: Unassuming, controversial shrine thought to be the tomb of either Jesus or a Muslim sage.
